Poclbm (PyOpenCL bitcoin miner) is a python GPU bitcoin miner that uses the [[OpenCL|OpenCL_miner]] framework to quickly perform the hashing computations.  Works with AMD - 4xxx and up, Nvidia - 8xxx and up, video cards.

##Download
[Latest miner.](http://github.com/downloads/m0mchil/poclbm/poclbm_py2exe_20110104.7z)

[Sources.](https://github.com/m0mchil/poclbm/archives/master)

##Flags to Use

ATI/AMD Radeon HD 5xxx cards (for example, HD 5770): use '-v -w128'

If you find the desktop laggy while mining, use '-f60'. This may decrease performance slightly.

Please update this section if you find better settings, or good settings for a card not listed here.

